A seven-months pregnant woman and her two sons have been shot by suspected bandits at their home in Arjijo village, Laikipia North constituency.Mukogodo East MCA Paul Shuel said the family was asleep on Monday night when an unknown number of bandits broke into their house and started shooting indiscriminately.Rose Kuraru, 25, was shot in the left leg and shoulder. Her sons Lodumu Kuraru, eight, and Salim Kuraru, five, were wounded in the chest and right leg, respectively.It is suspected to have been a revenge attack. A herder was shot dead last Thursday when a group drove away livestock at Ilng&rsquo;wesi lodge and shot at National Police Reservists. The mother and sons received first aid at Cottage Hospital, Nanyuki town, and were airlifted to Nairobi Hospital.